727994f-b.text:
165-04 South Road, at the S.E. corner of 165th Street, showing the John Case home, which belonged to his estate from 1873 to 1891.  William Case, a milkman, owned it in 1900.  It is said to be the oldest house in Jamaica.

Views 1, 2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1923

Views 3, 4: P.L. Sperr
March 30, 1932
